definitions.definition: A speech that sets the main theme of a conference or other gathering; a keynote speech or keynote address .
The main theme of a speech, a written work, or a conference.
The note on which a musical key is based; the tonic .

main_definition: A speech that sets the main theme of a conference or other gathering; a keynote speech or keynote address .
